Step 1: Create sales.csv on the local machine (See previous slide)
Step 2: Create a new S3 bucket with name yourname-sales-lambda-demo-2026
Step 3: Create Lambda function
Search for lambda -> Create function -> Author from scratch
Function name: sales_total_function
Runtime: Python 3.x
Permissions should be: Create a new role with basic Lambda permissions
Click Create
Go to Code tab and add the code shown on the next slide
After that, click Deploy
Step 4: Give Lambda permission to read from S3
In the Lambda function page, open the Configuration tab
Open Permissions
Click the execution role name shown there. This opens IAM.
In IAM, click Add permissions → Attach policies -> AmazonS3FullAccess
Click Add permissions button
Step 5: Configure S3 to trigger Lambda
Go back to S3
Open your bucket
Open the Properties tab
Scroll to Event notifications
Click Create event notification
Event notification name: sales-upload-trigger
Under event types, choose All object create events
Under Destination, choose Lambda function and select the sales-upload-trigger function
Save
Test :
Upload the sales.csv file in the S3 bucket
Check if the output file is created in the same bucket
